All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    AssaultParty
    Assault Party is constituted by Ordinary Thieves that are going to attack the museum.
    AssaultPartyElemLogging
    Util class used in GeneralRepository to represent each Assault Party element, the identification of the thief, its position in the line to the room in the Museum and a number representing the carrying of a canvas.
    AssaultPartyInterface
    Interface which provides communication to and from the Assault Party.
    AssaultPartyLogging
    Util class used in GeneralRepository to represent each Assault Party, its room target and the constituting elements.
    AssaultPartyMain
    Assault Party server of the Heist To The Museum.
    AssaultPartyProxyAgent
    Proxy Agent for the Assault Party, inherits the attributes and methods of both Master Thief and Ordinary Thief.
    AssaultPartyStub
    Stub to the Assault Party.
    ClientCom
    Communication manager - client side.
    CollectionSite
    Collection Site where intelligence and paintings are stored.
    CollectionSiteInterface
    Interface which provides communication to and from the Collection Site.
    CollectionSiteMain
    Collection Site server of the Heist To The Museum.
    CollectionSiteProxyAgent
    Proxy Agent for the Collection Site, inherits the attributes and methods of both Master Thief and Ordinary Thief.
    CollectionSiteStub
    Collection Site where Master Thief intelligence and paintings are stored.
    ConcentrationSite
    Concentration Site where ordinary thieves wait for orders.
    ConcentrationSiteInterface
    Interface which provides communication to and from the Concentration Site.
    ConcentrationSiteMain
    Concentration Site server of the Heist To The Museum.
    ConcentrationSiteProxyAgent
    Proxy Agent for the Concentration Site, inherits the attributes and methods of both Master Thief and Ordinary Thief.
    ConcentrationSiteStub
    Concentration Site where ordinary thieves wait for orders.
    Constants
    Constants to be used in the Heist To The Museum.
    GeneralRepository
    General Repository where logging occurs.
    GeneralRepositoryInterface
    Interface which provides communication to and from the General Repository.
    GeneralRepositoryMain
    General Repository server of the Heist To The Museum.
    GeneralRepositoryProxyAgent
    Proxy Agent for the General Repository, inherits the attributes and methods of both Master Thief and Ordinary Thief.
    GeneralRepositoryStub
    The General Repository, where all information is stored and logged.
    HeistToTheMuseum
    Distributed version of the Heist To The Museum.
    Logger
    Logger responsible for generating and filling the logging file of the simulation.
    MasterThief
    Master Thief, the thief that commands the heist.
    MasterThiefClone
    Interface which provides the states and methods to be overridden by the proxy agents of the Master Thief.
    Message
    Internal structure of the exchanged messages.
    MessageException
    Message exception.
    MessageType
    Type of the exchanged messages.
    Museum
    The Museum has rooms inside it.
    MuseumInterface
    Interface which provides communication to and from the Museum.
    MuseumMain
    Museum server of the Heist To The Museum.
    MuseumProxyAgent
    Proxy Agent for the Museum, inherits the attributes and methods of both Master Thief and Ordinary Thief.
    MuseumStub
    The Museum has rooms inside it.
    OrdinaryThief
    Ordinary Thief, one of the thieves involved in the heist.
    OrdinaryThiefClone
    Interface which provides the states and methods to be overridden by the proxy agents of the Ordinary Thief.
    OrdinaryThiefLogging
    Util class used in GeneralRepository to represent each Ordinary Thief, its identification, its situation and its maximum displacement.
    Room
    Rooms contains paintings that can be stolen by the Thieves attacking the museum.
    RoomLogging
    Util class used in GeneralRepository to represent the rooms, their number of paintings and the distance to them.
    ServerCom
    Communication manager - server side.
